<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN385-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai atu. tuṟai – vāḻttiyal. amparkiḻāṉ aruvantaiyaik kallāṭaṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN385">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>veḷḷi tōṉṟap puḷḷukkura liyampap</l>
<l>pulari viṭiyaṟ pakaṭupala vāḻttit</l>
<l>taṉkaṭait tōṉṟiṉu milaṉē piṟaṉkaṭai</l>
<l>yakaṉkaṭ ṭaṭārip pāṭukēṭ ṭaruḷi</l>
<l>vaṟaṉyā ṉīṅkal vēṇṭi yeṉṉarai</l>
<l>nīṉiṟañ citāar kaḷaintu</l>
<l>veḷiya tuṭīiyeṉ pacikaḷain tōṉē</l>
<l>kāviri yaṇaiyun tāḻnīrp paṭappai</l>
<l>nelviḷai kaḻaṉi yampar kiḻavō</l>
<l>ṉallaru vantai vāḻiyar pulliya</l>
<l>vēṅkaṭa viṟalvaraip paṭṭa</l>
<l>vōṅkal vāṉat tuṟaiyiṉum palavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="1">When Venus appeared, when bird voices word sounding, </l>
<l corresp="2">although right at dawn, praising the many bulls, </l>
<l>I appeared at his gate, he was not there. Graciously listening </l>
<l>to the song of [my] wide-eyed Taṭāri drum at the gate of another, (3f.) </l>
<l corresp="5">wanting me to be rid of drought from my middle </l>
<l corresp="6">he removed the blue-coloured rag, </l>
<l corresp="7">putting something white on [me] it was he who removed my hunger. </l>
<l corresp="9">The lord beyond there of the paddy-ripening fields </l>
<l corresp="8">by the hanging water garndens that touch upon the Kāviri, </l>
<l corresp="10">good Aruvantai may live to embrace [me] </l>
<l corresp="12">many more [days] than are [rain] drops in the high clouds </l>
<l corresp="11">that descend on the victorious mountain of Vēṅkaṭam. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
